    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>BRAZIL BANK MERGER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brazil's Banco Itau pays $872 million in auction for Banco do Estado do Parana (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>One of Brazil's largest banks, Banco Itau, paid $872 million in an auction for Banco do Estado do Parana, a bank in Brazil's Parana state, increasing Itau's base of seven million customers by more than a half million. Itau paid a 303 percent premium over the minimum price set at an auction, beating bids from two local rivals. Itau, which previously acquired the state banks of Minas Gerais and Rio de Janeiro, is also considered one of the main contenders in the coming auction of the Sao Paulo state bank, Banespa.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich</p>
      </block>
